<p>The provider rule type allows to filter for IP addresses, subnets or ASNs.</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>IP address</strong>
        <p>Enter an IP address which is not allowed to make any submissions.</p>
        <p>
            <u>Example:</u> <code>192.168.10.10</code> or <code>abcd:ef01::1</code>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Subnet</strong>
        <p>Enter a subnet with mask which is not allowed to make any submissions.</p>
        <p>
            <u>Example:</u> <code>192.168.10.0/24</code> or <code>abcd:ef01::/48</code>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>ASN</strong>
        <p>Enter an ASN which is not allowed to make any submissions. All IP addresses which belongs to this ASN will be blocked.</p>
        <p>
            <u>Example:</u> <code>AS123456</code>
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>
                {# @todo: update this help text and add a link to the config page #}
                To use the ASN subtype it is required to configure the MindMax database, otherwise, the ASN items will not have any effect.
            </strong>
        </p>
    </li>
</ul>

